today's forecast called for snow from the central plains to the middle mississippi valley. rain and thunderstorms will reach from the lower mississippi valley across eastern texas. highs will be in the 30s from the northern and central plains to northern new england. highs will generally reach the 50s and 60s west of the rockies, with 70s in southern california. highs also will reach the 50s and 60s from southern and central new mexico across louisiana and southern arkansas to the southern and middle atlantic coast, with 70s over the lower rio grande valley of texas
