hodel ``listened to their concerns about threats to the environment from phosphate mining, and human rights,'' and reiterated american support for estonian aspirations, said spokesman david prosperi
estonia is one of the three baltic countries who declared independence on the breakup of the czar's empire in 1917 and were taken over by the soviet union in 1940 under the nazi-soviet pact of 1939. the united states still accords diplomatic recognition to the governments-in-exile of the three countries, estonia, latvia and lithuania
