britain's major commercial banks cut their base lending rate by half a percentage point to 8.5 percent after the bank of england signaled that it wanted such a cut by cutting its own money market intervention rates
the cuts took the market by surprise and triggered a wave of buying, lifting share prices from their lowest levels, dealers said
the rate cut came as the pound moved above 3.10 west german marks and seemed to confirm a new unofficial government cap for the pound at that level, which was seen as a positive development, dealers said
but some dealers said the rate cut also raised worries about overheating in the economy
the market is very vulnerable to bad news at the moment,'' a dealer said
unemployment in britain fell to a seasonally adjusted 9.1 percent of the work force in february from 9.2 percent in january, the government said thursday
the figure was down from 11 percent in february 1987, the department of employment said
seasonally adjusted unemployment was estimated at 2.53 million people in february, down from a revised 2.56 million people in january and 3.07 million people in february 1987. up 3rd graf pvs, bentsen said ...</note>
the federal deposit insurance corp. is planning to pump about $1 billion of capital into first republicbank corp. to offset a two-day drain of deposits, according to a report published today
the dallas morning news quoted unidentified banking sources as saying the run on funds would force the fdic to transfer about $1 billion in interim assistance, perhaps as early as today
sources also said such interim assistance is likely to include a blanket guarantee of all deposits by the fdic
without a blanket guarantee from the fdic, the deposits are going to leave,'' a banking analyst who asked to remain unidentified told the newspaper. ``you have to stabilize the patient before you can do the surgery.''
officials of the bank and the fdic declined comment late wednesday on the report
meanwhile, texas sen. lloyd bentsen estimated it could cost up to $5 billion to prop up first republicbank, but he says federal regulators were prepared to help the bank holding company avoid a financial collapse
bentsen said wednesday he spoke with federal reserve chairman alan greenspan, robert l. clarke, the comptroller of the currency, and l. william seidman, chairman of the fdic
i've been assured that all of those financial institutions are standing by to help,'' bentsen said. ``they're going to do all they can to see that this situation is stabilized.''
bentsen said the senate banking committee gave him the $5 billion figure, but he also said he did not believe there were any definitive figures yet on the cost of a rescue plan
first republicbank, the state's biggest banking company, acknowledged tuesday it had been forced to seek federal aid because of a deteriorating loan portfolio and difficulty in raising deposits
a first republicbank spokesman said wednesday the bank experienced a runoff of deposits on tuesday, but that the situation apparently had stabilized. an earlier drain of deposits and customer defections had forced it to begin preliminary discussions with the fdic, the spokesman said
tuesday there was a significant amount of activity, and there were some deposit outflows,'' the spokesman said. ``but there were no lines or confusion in our branches or banks.''
the spokesman did not quantify the size of the deposit outflows
the fdic is prepared to assist with capital and the federal reserve with liquidity, bentsen said
each of these regulatory powers have assured me they will do everything they can that is necessary to keep that situation from unraveling,'' he said
bentsen said the agencies would ensure first republicbank branches statewide remained open, but would not comment on the status of the holding company
the nation's trade deficit widened slightly in january to $12.4 billion after two months of sharp improvements, the commerce department said today in a report that left financial markets uncertain
the dollar and the bond market rallied after the report, but gave back most of their gains after a few minutes
the excess of imports over exports was up from the $12.2 billion deficit in december
exports, which had propelled improvement in november and december, fell by 10 percent in january to $22.3 billion
analysts had expected a deterioration of the trade balance in january, noting that exports are traditionally down in that month
however, imports also fell in january, by 6 percent to $34.8 billion
thus, the deficit for the month _ eagerly followed by financial markets _ was somewhat better than most analysts had expected
within half an hour of the report's 8:30 a.m. est release, the treasury's benchmark 30-year bond was yielding 8.58 percent, little changed from 8.60 percent late wednesday. and the dollar was barely higher against the japanese yen, british pound and west german mark
on wednesday, the federal reserve said industrial production edged up 0.2 percent in february despite output reductions at auto factories and coal mines
economists said the gain, although slower than the january rise, represented good news for the economy and further dampened concerns about a severe slowdown in the aftermath of the october stock market crash
a more positive signal came from the commerce department, which said the housing industry after staggering for two months enjoyed an 8.9 percent gain in construction activity in february, the biggest rise in more than a year
with interest rates at low levels and the economy growing and no recession in sight, we think we have all the ingredients in place to generate a strong spring building season,'' said warren lasko, executive vice president of the mortgage bankers association
nevertheless, the news hurt the bond market, a barometer of interest rates and the economy. stronger growth implies future inflation, which erodes the value of fixed-income investments
the treasury's key 30-year issue fell $10 per $1,000 in face amount. its yield jumped from 8.51 percent to 8.60 percent, its highest level since late january
but the stock market closed largely higher. the dow jones average of 30 industrial stocks, which most of the day showed a modest loss, ended with a 16.91 point gain at 2,064.32 in slow trading
