i think the trade number was just what everybody liked,'' said philip c. puccio, manager of institutional trading at dillon, read &amp; co. in new york. ``it brought a sigh of relief.''
nevertheless, puccio and other trading strategists said investors still were reluctant to commit large amounts of cash to the stock market until the conclusion of so-called ``triple witching hour'' on friday
that quarterly event is so-named because of the near-simultaneous expiration of contracts to buy or sell stock-index futures, stock options and futures. it has played a role in wild price swings in the past
